text.__SUMMARY__: Angraecum eburneum is a species of orchid. Their common name the "comet orchid". They generally grow up to 2 meters in height and grows 10 to 15 flowers per plant. They are native to Madagascar, Comoros, Seychelles, Réunion, Mauritius, Kenya, and Tanzania.
text.Description: The white and green flower is 7.5 cm in size and is said to give off a pleasant smell. Flowering begins in early winter and takes several months.
text.Symbolism: Claire Waight Keller included the plant to represent Seychelles in Meghan Markle's wedding veil, which included the distinctive flora of each Commonwealth country.
